# Agent Rehydration

## Foundational Manifesto
### Version 1.0

---

> **Conversation memory preserves history.**
>
> **Agent Rehydration preserves continuity.**

---

# Why Agent Rehydration Matters

Artificial Intelligence is entering a new era.

Large Language Models are evolving beyond isolated conversations. Increasingly, they operate as autonomous agents capable of pursuing objectives, interacting with external systems, making decisions and performing meaningful work over extended periods of time.

This evolution introduces a fundamental challenge.

**How can an autonomous agent continue its work after an interruption without losing its operational identity?**

Traditional software can restart from a saved state.

Conversational AI can recover previous messages.

Autonomous agents require something more.

They require continuity.

---

# Beyond Conversation Memory

Conversation history is essential.

It preserves what has been said.

Summaries preserve what has been discussed.

Vector memories preserve information that may become relevant again.

All of these mechanisms are valuable.

Yet they primarily answer one question:

> **What happened?**

An autonomous agent must answer a different one.

> **What was I doing, and how do I continue doing it?**

Remembering information is not equivalent to reconstructing the operational state required to continue meaningful work.

Operational continuity extends beyond memory.

It encompasses the entire working state of an autonomous agent.

---

# Defining Agent Rehydration

Agent Rehydration is the discipline of preserving and reconstructing the operational continuity of autonomous AI agents.

Its objective is not merely to recover information.

Its objective is to restore the minimum operational state necessary for an agent to continue pursuing its objectives coherently after an interruption.

Operational state may include, among other elements:

- Identity
- Objectives
- Plans
- Constraints
- Working Memory
- Available Tools
- Permissions
- Execution Environment
- Dependencies
- Pending Tasks
- Operational Context
- Confidence

Different implementations may preserve different subsets of this information.

The principle remains the same:

**An interrupted agent should continue its work, not simply remember its past.**

---

# A Portable Concept

Future autonomous agents will not exist within a single model, framework or provider.

They will move across:

- AI models
- Cloud platforms
- Local devices
- Organizations
- Execution environments
- Time

Operational continuity should survive these transitions.

Agent Rehydration therefore describes a capability rather than an implementation.

It is intentionally independent of vendors, architectures, programming languages and AI frameworks.

---

# A Common Language

Many existing technologies already address parts of this challenge.

Checkpointing.

Workflow persistence.

State snapshots.

Session restoration.

Context management.

Task recovery.

Each contributes an important capability.

Agent Rehydration does not replace these approaches.

Instead, it provides a common conceptual framework capable of describing them as different strategies for preserving operational continuity.

Giving this broader concept a shared name enables clearer discussion, comparison and future standardization.

---

# Principles

Agent Rehydration should strive to be:

- Portable
- Vendor-neutral
- Explainable
- Inspectable
- Secure
- Incremental
- Verifiable
- Extensible

These principles are intentionally technology-agnostic.

They are expected to remain relevant as AI systems continue to evolve.

---

# An Open Initiative

Agent Rehydration is not a product.

It is not a protocol.

It is not a commercial platform.

It is not owned by any single organization.

It is an open conceptual initiative intended to encourage discussion, experimentation and collaboration around one emerging challenge:

**preserving operational continuity for autonomous AI agents.**

Everyone is invited to contribute.

---

# Looking Forward

As autonomous agents become increasingly capable, interruptions will become part of normal operation rather than exceptional events.

Operational continuity will become a fundamental capability of intelligent systems.

Memory alone will no longer be sufficient.

The future belongs to agents capable not only of remembering the past,

but of continuing the future.

---

# Closing Statement

History explains the past.

Continuity enables the future.

That is the difference.

That is Agent Rehydration.

